CHANGE tutorial.2.name:1 "完成星系勘察"
NEW tutorial.2.desc:1 "Well done! The first survey of a star system beyond our own has been completed. We now have access to planetary data that the astronomers on our homeworld could only dream of a mere generation ago."
OLD tutorial.2.desc:0 "Well done! The survey of our home system has been completed. We now have access to planetary data that the astronomers on our homeworld could only dream of a mere generation ago."
CN  tutorial.2.desc:1 "非常好！我们的母星系勘察好了。我们母星上一代宇航员在梦中才能收集的数据，现在已尽在掌握。"
CHANGE tutorial.2.desc:1 "非常好！我们母星以外的首个星系已经勘察完毕。我们母星上一代宇航员在梦中才能收集的数据，现在已尽在掌握。"
NEW tutorial.9.desc:1 "The resources generated by our homeworld will only take us so far. Luckily our §SScience Ship§! has just found a resource deposit on another world! The time has come to use our §SConstruction Ship§! to build a §SMining Station§!.\n\nMining Stations can be built within our borders and automatically collect §SMinerals§! and any §SStrategic Resources§! found on the bodies they orbit. Keep in mind that they have an £energy  §SEnergy Credit§! upkeep cost."
OLD tutorial.9.desc:1 "The resources generated by our homeworld will only take us so far. Luckily our §SScience Ship§! has just found a resource deposit on another world! The time has come to use our §SConstruction Ship§! to build a §SMining Station§!.\n\nMining Stations can be built within our borders and automatically collect §SMinerals§! and any §SStrategic Resources§! found on the bodies they orbit. Keep in mind that they have an £energy  §SEnergy Credit§! maintenance cost."
CN  tutorial.9.desc:1 "母星上生产的资源只够我们暂时使用，好在我们的§S科研船§!发现了一处资源矿藏！是时候用§S工程船§!建造一个§S采矿基地§!了。\n\n采矿基地可以在帝国境内建造，可自动采集其轨道天体上的§S矿物§!和§S战略资源§!。记住，它们需要£energy §S能源点数§!进行维护。"
CHANGE tutorial.9.desc:1 "母星上生产的资源只够我们暂时使用，好在我们的§S科研船§!发现了一处资源矿藏！是时候用§S工程船§!建造一个§S采矿基地§!了。\n\n采矿基地可以在帝国境内建造，可自动采集其轨道天体上的§S矿物§!和§S战略资源§!。记住，它们需要£energy §S能源点数§!进行维护。"
NEW tutorial.11.desc:0 "Surveyed worlds sometimes possess unique properties that make them valuable objects of research. These £physics  §SPhysics§!, £society  §SSociety§! or £engineering  §SEngineering§! resources can be collected by a §SResearch Station§!. My programming strongly compels me to compel you to build one.\n\nKeep in mind that §SResearch Stations§! can only be built within our borders, and have a upkeep cost in £energy  §SEnergy Credits§!."
OLD tutorial.11.desc:0 "Surveyed worlds sometimes possess unique properties that make them valuable objects of research. These £physics  §SPhysics§!, £society  §SSociety§! or £engineering  §SEngineering§! resources can be collected by a §SResearch Station§!. My programming strongly compels me to compel you to build one.\n\nKeep in mind that §SResearch Stations§! can only be built within our borders, and have a maintenance cost in £energy  §SEnergy Credits§!."
CN  tutorial.11.desc:0 "勘察过的星球有些会具有特殊性质，是非常好的研究项目。这些£physics §S物理§!，£society §S社会§!和£engineering §S工程§!资源可以用§S科研基地§!采集。我的程序强烈建议我强烈建议你建造一个科研基地。\n\n记住§S科研基地§!只能在帝国境内建造，它们需要£energy §S能源点数§!的维持费用。"
CHANGE tutorial.11.desc:0 "勘察过的星球有些会具有特殊性质，是非常好的研究项目。这些£physics §S物理§!，£society §S社会§!和£engineering §S工程§!资源可以用§S科研基地§!采集。我的程序强烈建议我强烈建议你建造一个科研基地。\n\n记住§S科研基地§!只能在帝国境内建造，它们需要£energy §S能源点数§!的维持费用。"
NEW tutorial.33.desc:1 "A healthy supply of §SMinerals§! and §SEnergy Credits§! is critical to the well-being of any interstellar power. We should take steps to increase our production of these resources.\n\nStations and Buildings cost Minerals to build and Energy Credits to maintain. The same is true for Ships, except that they have a Mineral upkeep cost as well. Both resources are produced by §SMining Stations§! or §SPlanetary Buildings§!."
OLD tutorial.33.desc:0 "A healthy supply of §SMinerals§! and §SEnergy Credits§! is critical to the well-being of any interstellar power. We should take steps to increase our production of these resources.\n\nShips, stations and buildings cost Minerals to build and Energy Credits to maintain. Both resources are produced by §SMining Stations§! or §SPlanetary Buildings§!."
CN  tutorial.33.desc:1 "充足的 §S矿物§! 资源与 §S能源点数§! 对于每个星际势力来说都是至关重要的。我们应该增加这些资源的生产。\n\n舰队，哨站和建筑都会花费矿物资源，同时需要能源点数维持他们的运行。这两种资源都可以通过 §S采矿基地§! 或者 §S行星建筑§!获得。"
NEW tutorial.33.desc:1 "充足的 §S矿物§! 资源与 §S能源点数§! 对于每个星际势力来说都是至关重要的。我们应该增加这些资源的生产。\n\n空间站和建筑都会花费矿物资源，同时需要能源点数维持他们的运行。飞船也是如此，而且飞船还需要花费矿物来维持。这两种资源都可以通过 §S采矿基地§! 或者 §S行星建筑§!获得。"
NEW tutorial.49.desc:1 "Good job. The ship design has been added to our database, and can now be produced by a §SStarbase§! that has been equipped with a §SShipyard§!."
OLD tutorial.49.desc:0 "Good job. The ship design has been added to our database, and can now be produced by a §SSpaceport§!."
CN  tutorial.49.desc:1 "干的好。新的船只设计已经添加到我们的数据库中，可以在§S太空港§!中进行生产。"
CHANGE tutorial.49.desc:1 "干的好。新的船只设计已经添加到我们的数据库中，可以在配备了§S船坞§的§S太空基地§!中进行生产。"
NEW tutorial.55.desc:3 "We have uncovered a §SStrategic Resource§!! §SStrategic Resources§! are, surprisingly enough, of strategic value. They give powerful bonuses to anyone possessing them. We should build a §SMining Station§! to procure this precious boon.\n\nDon't forget to build §SStarbases§! where appropriate to secure the resources within our borders. The effects of Strategic Resources do not stack, but controlling more than one source lets us trade the resource to another empire."
OLD tutorial.55.desc:2 "We have uncovered a §SStrategic Resource§!! §SStrategic Resources§! are, surprisingly enough, of strategic value. They are needed to construct and utilize certain powerful §SBuildings§! and §SSpaceport Modules§!. We should build a §SMining Station§! to procure this precious boon.\n\nDon't forget to build §SFrontier Outposts§! where appropriate to secure the resources within our borders."
CN  tutorial.55.desc:3 "我们找到了一处§S战略资源§!！§S战略资源§!具有很重要的战略意义（这还用说）。在建造和使用一些强力的§S建筑§!和§S太空港模块§!时就需要用到战略资源。我们最好建造一座§S采矿基地§!来采集这种宝贵的资源。\n\n不要忘记建造§S边境哨站§!。它可以确保我方疆界内的资源安全。"
CHANGE tutorial.55.desc:3 "我们找到了一处§S战略资源§!！§S战略资源§!具有很重要的战略意义。通过它们获得强大的奖励。我们应当建造一个§S采矿基地§!以获得这个宝贵恩赐。\n\n不要忘记建造§S太空基地§!保证这些资源位于我们境内。战略资源的作用不会叠加，但是控制多个来源可以将资源用于与其他帝国的交易中。"
NEW tutorial.560.desc:3 "A new technology has revealed that we already have a §SMining Station§! conveniently placed above a previously unknown §SStrategic Resource§!. These rare resources give powerful bonuses to whoever controls them. Two metaphorical avians, allegorically struck down by an imaginary projectile.\n\nMore information can be found in the §SSituation Log§! for a time. There are many more §SStrategic Resources§! left to discover in the galaxy, so keep on researching!"
OLD tutorial.560.desc:2 "A new technology has revealed that we already have a §SMining Station§! conveniently placed above a previously unknown §SStrategic Resource§!. These rare resources are required to construct and operate unique §SBuildings§! and §SSpaceport Modules§!. Two metaphorical avians, allegorically struck down by an imaginary projectile.\n\nMore information can be found in the §SSituation Log§! for a time. There are many more §SStrategic Resources§! left to discover in the galaxy, so keep on researching!"
CN  tutorial.560.desc:3 "一项新的技术表明，在我们已有的一个§S采矿基地§!下有一种珍贵的未知§S战略资源§!。这些资源十分珍贵，可以用来建造和使用§S建筑§!和§S太空港模块§!。这简直是宇宙版本的一“石”二“飞行器”啊。\n\n更多的信息已经记入§S情报日志§!。在银河系中还有很多§S战略资源§!等待我们去挖掘，继续探索吧！"
CHANGE tutorial.560.desc:3 "一项新的技术表明，在我们已有的一个§S采矿基地§!下有一种珍贵的未知§S战略资源§!。这些罕见的资源能给控制它们的人提供强大的奖励。真是一石二鸟。\n\n更多的信息已经记入§S情报日志§!。在银河系中还有很多§S战略资源§!等待我们去挖掘，继续探索吧！"
NEW tutorial.71.desc:1 "To overcome the vast distances that separate star systems, our scientists have developed the §SHyper Drive§!. This device permits travel at speeds far exceeding that of light between systems connected by hyperlanes.\n\nTravel along a hyperlane is extremely fast, but interstellar movement is restricted along the paths of the galactic hyperlane network. Safely entering hyperspace is only possible at the edge of a system, beyond the destabilizing effects of the star's gravity well."
OLD tutorial.71.desc:0 "To overcome the vast distances that separate star systems, our scientists have developed the §SHyper Drive§!. This device permits travel at speeds far exceeding that of light between systems connected by hyperlanes.\n\nAlthough travel along a hyperlane is extremely fast, a significant drawback of this FTL method is that interstellar travel is restricted along the paths of the galactic hyperlane network. On the other hand, jumping to hyperspace is possible anywhere within a star system."
CN  tutorial.71.desc:1 "为了克服遥远星系间的巨大距离，我们的科学家们发明了的§S超空间引擎§!。飞船装备了这种装置，就可以在超空间连接的两个星系中以超光速(FTL)的速度穿梭。\n\n虽然使用超空间进行移动速度极快，这种旅行方式有一项重大缺陷：星系旅行在银河系超维平面网络是受限制的。不过同时，在星系内部可以随时随地进入超空间。"
CHANGE tutorial.71.desc:1 "为了克服遥远星系间的巨大距离，我们的科学家们发明了的§S超空间引擎§!。飞船装备了这种装置，就可以在超空间连接的两个星系中以超光速(FTL)的速度穿梭。\n\n沿着超空间航道进行移动的速度非常快，但是受限于银河系的超空间航道网络。恒星重力井带来影响而导致不稳定，只有在星系边缘才能安全地进入超空间。"
